President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Judy Ansley as a Member of the Board of Directors of the United States Institute of Peace. Ansley has a strong background in national security, having served as Assistant to the President and Deputy National Security Advisor at the National Security Council. She also has over 20 years of experience working in various positions in the U.S. Senate, including as National Security Advisor to Senator John Warner and as a member of the staff of the Senate Armed Services Committee. Ansley holds an M.A. from the Fletcher School of Law and Diplomacy and a B.A. from Tufts University.

President Obama also intends to nominate Ann Begeman as a Member of the Surface Transportation Board. Begeman has been the Minority Staff Director of the Senate Committee on Commerce, Science, and Transportation since 2009. She has extensive experience in surface transportation issues, having worked on multiple legislative initiatives related to rail, motor carrier, and pipeline safety matters. Begeman holds a B.S. in Business Administration from the University of South Dakota.